message: The problem with the stats is that Bernie's ground game usually doesn't start picking up steam until the week before the primary. He far exceeded polls this past weekend. He did better than polls suggested he would in Arizona, despite the fiasco that occurred in that state, as well as in Utah and Idaho. He's been outperforming polls this entire election, so don't count him out yet.
